Encode Sans Semi Expanded Thin Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Thin.ttf)

STAT

static font

Variable font must have a STAT table.

No check of STAT table for static fonts included, yet. Static fonts do not need to have a STAT table. It is only recommended by Microsoft, not required.
More infos here:
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/stat

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Thin', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Thin Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Thin', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Thin Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded Thin'.

Pass

Encode Sans Semi Expanded ExLight Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded ExtraLight' ≠ 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded ExLight' (NID 1).

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Light Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded Light'.

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Regular', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Medium Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded Medium'.

Encode Sans Semi Expanded SmBd Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded SemiBold' ≠ 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded SmBd' (NID 1).

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Bold (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 8 is 'Impallari Type', but should be one of these: 'Monotype Imaging Inc.', 'Monotype Imaging Inc', 'Monotype ITC Inc.', 'Monotype Hong Kong Limited', 'Monotype Limited', 'Monotype KK', 'Monotype Solutions India Private Limited', 'Monotype GmbH', 'MyFonts Inc.', 'MyFonts Inc', 'Fontsmith Ltd.', 'Fontsmith Ltd'.

Error

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Encode Sans Semi Expanded Black Regular (EncodeSansSemiExpanded-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Semi Expanded Black'.

Pass
